So far, yet so close

By Chinese Academy of Social Sciences

Chinese love of the country with a pattern of difference, a person's interpersonal alienation, "like the surface of the open halo, " from their spread to the surrounding, circle by circle, according to the distance with their own close to divide the distance. At the beginning of the COVID-19, the distant cries did not seem to touch the chord of our hearts, we are still immersed in the joy of home and the New Year.

January 25, the first day of the Lunar New Year. I have never been so anxious to see the news in the news, to see the report of the Shanghai medical team's expedition to Wuhan, I have a sour nose, suffocated myself at this time and space have a warm blood but no effective skills to go to the front, only in the house to answer the call to be as far as possible not to cause trouble to others honest.

I first learned about Wuhan COVID-19 on January 19, from my graduate student's Group: "Sisters, Wuhan News is so big, how come no one cares about me? " I addressed the bed of Li Daya in the group. Usually thin and upright her "sense of presence" is very low, we went to school is for a bath card, or about the ideal of life of the illusory issue, no one to let who, because we know we will meet again.

"You are invulnerable to poison. "

"You talk to prove you're okay. ".

I was on duty in Beijing at the time, Beijing no waves, home there is no epidemic, busy with desk work on the past. However, when I went home, Caixin, Sanlian and other media exposed the true situation of the front line one after another, I was alarmed.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
When four new cases of COVID-19 infection were confirmed in Shanghai, Li Daya alerted mews in the group, telling her to pay attention, and I began to pay close attention to these outbreaks. Learning from the news and in the media, I began to brush up on this aspect of the news, like watching TV from morning to night, the more I understand, the more I think it is not just a virus so simple. At the same time, I also saw the Huazhong University of Science and Technology Affiliated Tongji Hospital and Xiehe Hospital unite all the hospitals in Wuhan, directly over the Wuhan Municipal Commission of Health and Family Planning, openly asking for help from the public. At first I thought it was an official act, it turned out to be the last straw for them to save themselves.

"The announcements from these hospitals are all true, and I made some of them. Our colleagues' husbands, as soon as they interviewed the medical staff, started crying. They were really short. They were short of supplies! " Li Daya told us in the group.

Grandma Ou has been on the move, and her friends in Shanghai have started to collect supplies. Taurus and I are very different. She is the hot girl of Hunan, always think of to do, as a conservative Taurus I just look askance but envy.

Our group's voluntary fund-raising began on January 24th, New Year's Eve.

Li Daya: "Huihui, do you have the resources of goggles? "

"okay, I'll make the call. ".

And that connection began our fundraising journey. From Li Daya's first-line News and past experience in dealing with SARS, we have reached a consensus: Can Not donate money, all into the most scarce materials straight to the front line. With a wide network of contacts, ou quickly connected with the resources of goggles. At 18:37 on January 25, he raised 947 pairs of goggles. I learned that her group and various friends were collecting supplies, and everywhere asked for Wuhan Hospital and personal contact information.

I began to have some misgivings and felt that in times of crisis it was better not to do many things than to do them wrong. Is the source of the goggles reliable? Is Everyone's money targeted? A series of question marks began in my mind. After work, the fact that I have to mature and heavy, think twice, mind your own business can be less wrong. But when I was left in front of Li Daya and Ou Lo these erstwhile peers, I decided to put aside worries, can do things, can voice voice, a hot, a light, do not have to wait for the torch. So I put the point can think of display in the group: 1. Make a donation instead of a donation; 2. Li Daya is responsible for making sure that the materials of the hospitals in Wuhan have been substantially improved, and if they have been improved, they will be sent to the surrounding counties and cities. 3. Find reliable supplies (purchase resources) , preferably in kind, to the front of the doctor to verify; 4. Keep a close eye on official developments to prevent civilian goods from blocking official roads.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the early morning of January 24, I edited a friend circle. Unexpectedly, I quickly got the attention of my younger brother and friends. I pulled in a few small groups. On the younger brother's side, I pulled in a girl who was studying abroad in Ireland. She said she was from Wuhan, at present, there are Chinese here who are willing to collectively raise money and materials but can not find the docking party. So she sent us their message. She said that she is from Wuhan. These are all things that should be done. On the other side was my friend, young slash teacher Xu, who told her friends in Beijing and Xi'an to start raising money around to donate. From New Year's Eve to the first day of the New Year, the two groups have not stopped communicating.

What worries me most is that the materials found spontaneously do not conform to the medical specifications. Because of the previous reports and relevant knowledge, I am mainly responsible for identifying the specifications of the materials found by everyone, and through Li Daya contact line doctors directly check.

At that time, the most Popular Front for help is the need for masks. I asked two of my medical friends, the final determination is the most able to help the first-line health care workers are disposable medical masks, N95 protective masks. I also found it in the article "Wuhan Medical Supplies: What can we do? " In Sanlian life weekly, at present, many hospitals on the Wuhan Front Line are raising medical supplies for the society: Medical Protective Masks need to meet the standards of YY0469-2010 and Gb19083-2010, and masks that fail to meet this standard will have one less layer of blue non-woven fabric than those with the same specifications, but it is this non-woven fabric that allows medical surgical masks to be more resistant to bacteria than normal dust masks. During this time, I also contacted my colleagues in the media to see if there was any way to mobilize together. Finally, the end of the screen sent "thank you Niu teacher, I am Wuhan. " When my tears brushed down, I feel the distance of the ripple pushed to my front.

So, from the 30th night to the first day of the whole day. Finally, 1,113 yuan went directly to the Wuhan Red Cross Society of Hubei, 1,133 yuan went to the General Affairs Office of the Wuhan Union Hospital, and 4,200 yuan went to the Department of gastroenterology of Wuhan Central Hospital, 1,400 pairs of shoe covers were mailed to the Gutian Park of Wuhan Fourth Hospital.

Later, Li Daya sent us a letter of thanks from frontline doctors on Wechat. Constantly jump out of the information to raise supplies, quickly to thank the wechat brush away, but I still feel the ripples in the distance in a circle near me..

As of this article, the group is still actively collecting the lack of materials in Wuhan County and city. Li Daya told us: "Wuhan five hospitals have already got the materials, many manufacturers directly unified deployment requisition, but deployment takes time, so the overall situation is still short, especially the county. ". "On Ou's side, Dr. Liu Qiong of Tongji Hospital in Wuhan sent a message: "Some of the government's aid has arrived. "

POSTSCRIPT:

Private fund-raising is still the existence of scattered material channels, material quality is difficult to predict, as well as can effectively reach the situation. We now know that the situation on the front line has improved, but there is still a shortage, especially in the counties, where the government prioritizes the large hospitals in Wuhan, which are overcrowded, and where deployment takes time and the county level cities can not accommodate it.
